        "title": "Comparing two lists and fetching child objects",
        "body": "<p>I have 2 lists. One, with just the parent Objects and the other which may have its child objects. <\/p>\n\n<p>Since these lists can be huge, I needed a way to fetch just the child objects by comparing the two lists in something better than <code>O(n^2)<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p>The condition for an object to be a child object is it should have its parent objects name as its base. eg: 'abcd' would be a child object of 'abc'.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; childList=new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\nfor(String parent: parentList){\n  for(String child: childList){\n    if(child.matches(parent + \"(.*)\"))\n      childList.add(child)\n  }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>With like 14k objects, this was taking like 10 seconds. Can someone help me optimize this<\/p>\n",
